body:
**Description**

I tried to draw a circle with an odd diameter and it does not look like a circle;
I guess negative distances are rounded differently, but I am not sure how to fix this.

**Code**

```c#
namespace ImageDemo
{
    using SkiaSharp;

    public class Program
    {
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            var bm = new SKBitmap(9, 9, false);
            var can = new SKCanvas(bm);
            var paint = new SKPaint();
            paint.Color = SKColors.Gray;
            paint.IsStroke = true;

            //draw a pattern for easier reference
            for (int i = 0; i < 9; i++)
            {
                for (int j = 0; j < 9; j++)
                {
                    if ((i + j) % 2 == 0)
                    {
                        can.DrawPoint(i, j, paint);
                    }
                }
            }
            paint.Color = SKColors.Blue;
            can.DrawPoint(4, 4, paint);
            can.DrawCircle(4, 4, 3.5f, paint);
            var data = bm.Encode(SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 90);
            var stream = File.Open("test.png", FileMode.Create);
            data.SaveTo(stream);
            stream.Close();
        }
    }
}



```

**Expected Behavior**

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/306107/219901245-8b869567-6e87-49be-b643-85fad58875c0.png) or 
